<title>PORTUGAL: Bank/Portugal cuts repo rate to 5.5 percent.</title>
<headline>Bank/Portugal cuts repo rate to 5.5 percent.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1997-08-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bank of Portugal cut 20 basis points off its main money market rates on Monday.</p>
<p>It set a fixed-rate repurchase pact at 5.5 percent, down from 5.7 percent previously.</p>
<p>It reduced its drain, or absorption rate to 5.2 percent from 5.4 percent and lowered its emergency lending rate to 7.2 percent from 7.4 percent previously.  </p>
<p>Bids for the repo funds must be received by 1415 GMT.</p>
<p>--Lisbon bureau 3511-3150035</p>
</text>
